  "text": "The canonical patterns for deploying new services are documented across the Kubernetes repositories as follows:\n\n## 1. API Type Definition (Authoritative)\n\nThe authoritative Deployment struct is defined in **github.com/sg-evals/api--v0.32.0** at **apps/v1/types.go** (lines 358-372). This is the official API definition used throughout the Kubernetes ecosystem. The repository README explains that 'api' is the canonical location of the Kubernetes API definition and serves as a dependency for client-go. The Deployment struct is defined with three main fields: TypeMeta, ObjectMeta (metadata), and DeploymentSpec (specification of desired behavior), along with DeploymentStatus.\n\n## 2. Client-Side Code Pattern\n\nThe canonical Go code example showing how to create Deployments is located in **github.com/sg-evals/client-go--v0.32.0** at **examples/create-update-delete-deployment/main.go**. This example demonstrates the complete lifecycle of Deployment management:\n\n- **Creating a Deployment** (line 103): Uses the Deployments client from the clientset with `deploymentsClient.Create(context.TODO(), deployment, metav1.CreateOptions{})`\n- **Updating a Deployment** (lines 125-137): Demonstrates the recommended pattern using `retry.RetryOnConflict` to handle concurrent updates safely\n- **Listing Deployments** (line 146): Uses `deploymentsClient.List(context.TODO(), metav1.ListOptions{})`\n- **Deleting a Deployment** (lines 157-160): Uses `deploymentsClient.Delete()` with proper propagation policy\n\nThe example creates a Deployment with 2 replicas running nginx:1.12, showing proper configuration of ObjectMeta (name), DeploymentSpec (replicas, selector, template), and PodSpec (containers).\n\n## 3. Developer Documentation\n\nThe deployment workflow is documented in multiple places:\n\n- **Main examples guide** in **github.com/sg-evals/client-go--v0.32.0** at **examples/README.md** explains that the 'Managing resources with API' example teaches Create, Get, Update, and Delete operations for Deployment resources.\n\n- **Specific deployment documentation** in **github.com/sg-evals/client-go--v0.32.0** at **examples/create-update-delete-deployment/README.md** provides:\n  - Step-by-step instructions for running the example\n  - Explanation of each operation (Create, Update, List, Delete)\n  - Expected output and verification steps\n  - Troubleshooting guidance\n  - Best practices for handling concurrent updates using the retry utility\n\nThese resources establish the canonical deployment pattern: define a Deployment object with proper metadata and spec, use the client library's Deployments() method to get a client for a namespace, and invoke Create/Update/List/Delete operations with appropriate options. The pattern emphasizes using `retry.RetryOnConflict` for safe updates in environments with concurrent modifications."
}

